## Agent Guidance

When developing, periodically ask:
- "Am I following a skill's steps manually that could be a function call?"
- "Am I writing the same boilerplate pattern for the 3rd+ time?"
- "Could `TOOL --audit code` or `TOOL --lang audit` catch this automatically?"

If yes, create the infrastructure first, then use it.

## Infrastructure Locations

Tools should import via `interface/` (facade layer), not directly from `logic/`:

| Purpose | Interface Import | Internal Location |
|---------|-----------------|-------------------|
| Code quality | `from interface.audit import run_full_audit` | `logic/audit/code_quality.py` |
| Status formatting | `from interface.status import fmt_status, fmt_warning` | `logic/turing/status.py` |
| Retry/backoff | `from interface.utils import retry` | `logic/utils/progress.py` |
| Preflight checks | `from interface.utils import preflight` | `logic/utils/preflight.py` |
| File cleanup | `from interface.utils import cleanup_old_files` | `logic/utils/cleanup.py` |
| Fuzzy suggestions | `from interface.utils import suggest_commands` | `logic/utils/fuzzy.py` |
| Logging | `from interface.utils import SessionLogger` | `logic/utils/logging.py` |
| Task management | `from tool.TODO.interface.main import todo_add` | `tool/TODO/logic/store.py` |
| Import auditing | `TOOL --audit imports` | `logic/lang/audit_imports.py` |
| Caching | `logic/audit/utils.py` AuditManager | Internal only |
